out how do we make the cost of care more effective.</div></div><div data-time="3764.63" class="caption-line" id="cp-913"><div class="caption-line-time">62:44</div><div class="caption-line-text">And there are ways of doing it.</div></div><div data-time="3766.7" class="caption-line" id="cp-914"><div class="caption-line-time">62:46</div><div class="caption-line-text">So at — at Cleveland Clinic, one of the
best health care systems in the world, they</div></div><div data-time="3772.61" class="caption-line" id="cp-915"><div class="caption-line-time">62:52</div><div class="caption-line-text">actually provide great care cheaper than average.
And the reason they do is because they do</div></div><div data-time="3779.09" class="caption-line" id="cp-916"><div class="caption-line-time">62:59</div><div class="caption-line-text">some smart things. They — they say, if a
patient's coming in, let's get all the doctors</div></div><div data-time="3783.92" class="caption-line" id="cp-917"><div class="caption-line-time">63:03</div><div class="caption-line-text">together at once, do one test instead of having
the patient run around with 10 tests. Let's</div></div><div data-time="3790.9" class="caption-line" id="cp-918"><div class="caption-line-time">63:10</div><div class="caption-line-text">make sure that we're providing preventive
care so we're catching the onset of something</div></div><div data-time="3794.87" class="caption-line" id="cp-919"><div class="caption-line-time">63:14</div><div class="caption-line-text">like diabetes. Let's — let's pay providers
on the basis of performance as opposed to</div></div><div data-time="3802.74" class="caption-line" id="cp-920"><div class="caption-line-time">63:22</div><div class="caption-line-text">on the basis of how many procedures they've
— they've engaged in. Now, so what this</div></div><div data-time="3810.26" class="caption-line" id="cp-921"><div class="caption-line-time">63:30</div><div class="caption-line-text">board does is basically identifies best practices
and says, let's use the purchasing power of</div></div><div data-time="3815.92" class="caption-line" id="cp-922"><div class="caption-line-time">63:35</div><div class="caption-line-text">Medicare and Medicaid to help to institutionalize
all these good things that we do.</div></div><div data-time="3821.63" class="caption-line" id="cp-923"><div class="caption-line-time">63:41</div><div class="caption-line-text">And the fact of the matter is that when "Obamacare"
is fully implemented, we're going to be in</div></div><div data-time="3828.13" class="caption-line" id="cp-924"><div class="caption-line-time">63:48</div><div class="caption-line-text">a position to show that costs are going down.
And over the last two years, health care premiums</div></div><div data-time="3835.47" class="caption-line" id="cp-925"><div class="caption-line-time">63:55</div><div class="caption-line-text">have gone up, it's true, but they've gone
